</div>
</div>
</td>
<td>
<div class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px;">
<div class="thumb" style="padding: 39px 0; width: 150px;">
<div style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 120px;"><a href="/wiki/File:A_Tutorial_on_the_Zachman_Architecture_Framework.jpg" class="image" title="A Tutorial on the Zachman Architecture Framework.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/A_Tutorial_on_the_Zachman_Architecture_Framework.jpg/120px-A_Tutorial_on_the_Zachman_Architecture_Framework.jpg" width="120" height="67" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
<div class="gallerytext">
<p>A Tutorial on the Zachman Architecture Framework</p>
</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>The Department of Veterans Affairs in the new Millennium was planning to implement a Enterprise Architecture full based on the Zachman Framework.</p>
<ul>
<li>The Zachman Framework was used as a reference model to initiate a Enterprise Architecture Planning in 2001.</li>
<li>Somewhere in between the VA Zachman Framework Portal was constructed.</li>
<li>This VA Zachman Framework Portal is still in use as a reference model for example in the determination of EA information collected from various business and project source documents.</li>
<li>Now somewhere in the past this "A Tutorial on the Zachman Architecture Framework".</li>
</ul>
<p>Eventually a Enterprise Architecture Repository is created at the macro level by the Zachman framework and at a cell level by the Meta-model outlined below.<sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34" title=""><span>[</span>35<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<div class="center">
<div class="thumb tnone">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:602px;"><a href="/wiki/File:VA_EA_Meta-Model_Cell_Details_Enlarged.jpg" class="image" title="VA EA Meta-Model Cell Details Enlarged."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/VA_EA_Meta-Model_Cell_Details_Enlarged.jpg/600px-VA_EA_Meta-Model_Cell_Details_Enlarged.jpg" width="600" height="390" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:VA_EA_Meta-Model_Cell_Details_Enlarged.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
VA EA Meta-Model Cell Details Enlarged.</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><a name="Criticism" id="Criticism"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Zachman_framework&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Criticism">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Criticism</span></h2>
<p>The primary strength of the Zachman Framework is that it explicitly shows that many <a href="/wiki/View_model" title="View model">views</a> needs to be addressed by <a href="/wiki/Enterprise_architecture" title="Enterprise architecture">enterprise architecture</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-GASLSJ03_11-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GASLSJ03-11" title=""><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup> It also has some potential problems:</p>
<ul>
<li>The Zachman framework can lead to a heavy documented approach&#160;: Each of the thirty cells of the framework needs to be supported by some kind of artefact, which can need a lot of documentation.<sup id="cite_ref-GASLSJ03_11-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GASLSJ03-11" title=""><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
</ul>
